description: Seven cops in Rajasthan's Bhiwadi have been suspended for illicitly tracking the location of their female SP, Jyeshtha Maitreyi, through her mobile phone for a month. The investigation, initiated by the SP herself, revealed the unauthorized surveillance. Higher authorities are seeking reports to understand the intent behind this act, possibly leading to further legal action.
title: 7 cops snooped on woman SP in Rajasthan, suspended

description: In Haryana's recent elections, 13 out of 90 constituencies saw winning margins under 2%. The BJP secured six of these, with the narrowest victory by 32 votes in Uchana Kalan. The Congress also had six tight wins, while INLD won one seat by a slim margin.
title: Haryana assembly elections: Win margin below 2% in 13 seats

description: Thirteen women have been elected to the Haryana assembly, equaling the record from the 2014 polls. BJP and Congress lead with five and seven women legislators respectively. Notable winners include Savitri Jindal and Vinesh Phogat. AAP fielded 11 women but secured no seats. Newcomers include Arti Rao and Pooja Chaudhary.
title: In Haryana, only second time, 13 women MLAs in House of 90

description: Congress's narrow focus on issues like employment and Agnipath overlooked persistent Jat vs non-Jat dynamics in Haryana, leading to BJP's unexpected victory. Infighting among Congress leaders and lack of strategic campaign design were also significant factors in their defeat.
title: Infighting, Jat tilt put paid to Congress hopes in Haryana

description: Former Haryana CM Bhupinder Singh Hooda, despite having control over ticket distribution, failed to secure a majority for Congress in recent state polls. Critics attribute the setback to his centralisation of power, departure of senior party members, and his controversial leadership decisions.
title: Hooda's moves end in anti-climax as state stalwart loses the plot again

description: The ITAT ruled that an individual's US income is taxable in India due to his residential status in both countries. Applying the 'tie-breaker test' under the India-US tax treaty, the tribunal determined that his 'centre of vital interest' was in India, thus making his US income taxable.
title: Man declares income of 9.5k, pays tax on 43.5L after US earnings added

description: President Droupadi Murmu presented the Dadasaheb Phalke Award to veteran actor Mithun Chakraborty and acknowledged winners of the 70th National Film Awards, including AR Rahman, Rishab Shetty, Nithya Menen, and Manasi Parekh. She emphasized Indian cinema's diversity and called for more women-led development in the industry.
title: Film industry needs more women-led development: President Murmu

description: Congress candidate Vinesh Phogat, a wrestler, triumphed in the Julana seat, defeating BJP's Captain Yogi Bairegi by about 6,000 votes. Despite trailing in some counting rounds, she ultimately secured 65,080 votes. Phogat attributed her win to a long struggle and a victory for women, promising future development for her constituency.
title: Golden moment: Vinesh wins round one on political debut

description: New Delhi's government deregistered over 59 lakh vehicles, mainly targeting diesel vehicles older than 10 years and petrol vehicles exceeding 15 years. With two-wheelers forming the majority, 39 lakh out of the total vehicles were two-wheelers. The move follows a Supreme Court directive to enforce the NGT order on deregistering overaged vehicles.
title: 59 lakh+ old city vehicles deregistered in 6 years

description: BJP replaced its long-time Chief Minister Manohar Lal Khattar with Nayab Singh Saini, an OBC leader, ahead of the Haryana assembly elections. This move led to a significant consolidation of non-Jat votes, resulting in BJP's highest seat tally and vote share of 39.9%. Congress's internal divisions and BJP's strategic campaigning aided this historic third consecutive win.
title: Haryana assembly elections: In season 3, BJP does better than 2014 show

description: The term 'Aya Ram Gaya Ram' originated in Haryana in 1967 due to an Independent MLA, Gaya Lal, switching parties multiple times in a day. Coined by former CM Rao Birender Singh, the phrase symbolizes political defection and continues to be relevant even after anti-defection laws were enacted.
title: 'Aya ram gaya ram': How Gaya Lal set the tone for turncoats

description: India's elephant population has decreased by almost 20% from 19,825 in 2017 to 15,887, as shown by the latest estimation conducted by the Wildlife Institute of India and state forest departments. This significant drop is attributed to the change in counting methods, from a headcount in 2017 to DNA analysis in 2022-23.
title: New DNA analysis shows 20% dip in elephant population

description: Dushyant Chautala’s JJP faced a massive defeat in the state polls, failing to win a single seat and seeing a drastic drop in vote share from 15% to less than 1%. Despite this, prominent political families including Chautala's still secured seats in the assembly.
title: Deputy CM to near-oblivion for Dushyant, 4 other ‘Lal’ dynasts make it to house

description: Nagaland CM Neiphiu Rio urges EAM S Jaishankar to stop a UK auction of a 19th-century Naga human skull, calling it dehumanizing and colonial violence. The skull was withdrawn from the auction at Pitt Rivers Museum's intervention, but its cancellation remains uncertain. A Naga professor highlighted ongoing issues with ancestral remains in private collections.
title: Stop UK auction of Naga skull, CM urges Centre

description: AAP secured a surprising victory in Doda, J&K but failed to win any seats in Haryana despite contesting 88 seats and extensive campaigning by Arvind Kejriwal. AAP's vote share remained at 1.8%, with 87 candidates losing their deposits. Kejriwal emphasized that election results highlight the importance of not being overconfident.
title: Neither sympathy nor vote, AAP fails to open its account

description: In the 1990s, Narendra Modi began his political journey as BJP's general secretary in Haryana, focusing on building the party's presence. His dedication led to significant electoral victories, including the 2024 elections. Modi's rallies in Haryana demonstrated strong support, with BJP achieving a hat-trick in the state. He referred to Haryana as his 'second home.'
title: PM Modi's Haryana connection continues to deliver for BJP

description: Nayab Singh Saini's appointment as Haryana's CM has revitalized BJP, overcoming anti-incumbency and capturing a significant share of SC/BC votes. His strategic moves and accessible leadership style have bolstered party confidence and neutralized Congress's challenges.
title: Nayab Singh Saini shining, set for lead role after cameo as CM

description: The New York Jets owner Woody Johnson has dismissed head coach Robert Saleh, with reports indicating that he was escorted out by security personnel. This sudden decision has raised questions about the stability of the team's coaching staff and management. Saleh’s tenure, which started in 2021, aimed at rebuilding the struggling franchise.
title: Was Saleh's dismissal a power play or a necessary move?

description: A new book by Bob Woodward reveals that President Joe Biden privately calls Donald Trump and other world leaders derogatory names, with Trump labeled as "that f**king a**hole." Additionally, Biden criticizes Obama’s handling of the Crimea crisis and uses profanity in private meetings. Kamala Harris was once concerned about Biden's isolation, the book revealed.
title: Joe Biden refers to Trump as 'that f**king a**hole' behind the doors, reveals book

description: Meghan Markle made a bold solo appearance at a Los Angeles red carpet event, donning a previously worn red dress, signaling her independence from the Royal family and readiness for Hollywood. Despite rumors of marital issues with Prince Harry, close friends claim they are not divorcing but pursuing separate professional paths.
title: Meghan Markle sends a coded message to the Royal family: 'I am not hiding'

description: After President Droupadi Murmu sent messages to Chinese President Xi Jinping on the 75th Anniversary of China, Foreign Ministry Spokesperson Mao Ning emphasised the country's willingness to strengthen communication and mutual trust with India, aiming to promote a stable development of the China-India relationship.
title: After Prez Murmu's message, China says 'ready' to improve ties with India

description: Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu announced that Israeli forces have successfully targeted and eliminated potential successors to the deceased Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah. Defence minister Yoav Gallant also indicated that Hashem Safieddine, a likely successor, had likely been 'eliminated'. Safieddine, like Nasrallah, is a cleric and has served as the head of Hezbollah's executive council and its military operations body, the Jihad Council.
title: We took out Nasrallah's replacement: Israeli PM Netanyahu

description: Mohamad Yousuf Tarigami of CPI(M) wins his fifth consecutive term in Kulgam constituency, defeating Jamaat-e-Islami candidate Sayar Reshi. Tarigami received 33,390 votes while Reshi got 25,639 votes. Tarigami, who is supported by various parties except BJP, has held this seat since 1996. National Conference did not field a candidate this time.
title: 5th straight win for CPM’s Tarigami in Kulgam

description: Early celebration at Congress headquarters in New Delhi turned somber as BJP gained ground in the Haryana assembly polls, ultimately securing a third consecutive win. Despite initial optimism and celebrations, Congress supporters gradually left their office, facing the reality of the vote count shift. Former leaders like Bhupinder Hooda remained hopeful, but the trends told a different story.
title: How ecstasy quickly turned into agony at Congress HQ

description: Decisive mandates in Haryana and J&K diminished the relevance of smaller regional parties like JJP, INLD, AAP, PDP, Jamaat-e-Islami, and AIP. JJP was decimated, INLD saw key defeats, and PDP struggled to retain its influence, highlighting major shifts in voter preferences.
title: Smaller parties lose out in bipolar poll

description: AIBA has requested CJI D Y Chandrachud to establish guidelines for judicial conduct following Justice R Subramanian's unprofessional outburst at senior advocate P Wilson. AIBA also called for a Supreme Court judge-led monitoring committee to review virtual court proceedings, highlighting the need for complaint redressal mechanisms.
title: Frame judicial conduct norms: Bar body after judge outburst

description: BJP secures 29 seats in Jammu region in the J&K assembly elections, with nearly 26% vote share but fails to form a government. Significant winners include Shagun Parihar and Shakti Raj Parihar, amidst challenges from Pakistan-backed terrorism and violence affecting various constituencies.
title: Jammu and Kashmir assembly elections 2024: Valley too far for BJP

description: In a surprising twist, BJP secured a comfortable majority in the Haryana elections, obtaining 48 seats against Congress's 37, despite strong anti-incumbency. Congress faced internal issues and miscalculations, while BJP's successful strategy targeted OBC voters and fragmented Dalit votes, ensuring a third consecutive term.
title: Hoodannit? Haryana results mystery leaves Congress clueless

description: NC vice-president Omar Abdullah expressed optimism about collaborating with the Centre after PM Modi praised NC's performance in J&K polls. Abdullah stressed the need for restoring J&K's statehood soon and emphasized a non-partisan approach for governance. He urged for cooperative relations with the Centre to ensure development and good governance for all regions in J&K.
title: Hope PM Modi, Amit Shah keep vow to restore statehood: Omar Abdullah

description: Congress has raised serious complaints regarding the integrity of the counting process and functionality of EVMs in Haryana. Party spokespersons allege manipulation and bias in favor of BJP, while EC rejects these claims, emphasizing the speed and validity of their counting updates.
title: Congress questions integrity of counting, alleges conspiracy

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath unveiled a multi-coloured logo for the 2025 Maha Kumbh in Prayagraj, symbolising religious and economic prosperity. The design features mythological and religious elements like the Akshayvat tree and Lord Hanuman, representing Sanatan Dharma's essence. It reflects the event's spiritual and cultural significance, including religious sites along the Sangam.
title: Maha Kumbh logo signifies religious, economic prosperity

description: BJP's third consecutive victory in Haryana highlights the unshakeable faith in PM Modi's double-engine government, appreciated by farmers, the poor, backward classes, soldiers, and youth. Amit Shah criticized Congress for divisive politics, while Rajnath Singh emphasized BJP's effective governance and development.
title: Haryana win marks faith in BJP: Amit Shah

description: PDP chief Mehbooba Mufti conceded a bruising defeat in J&K's recent assembly elections, securing only three seats. She pledged not to contest until J&K's statehood is restored following the abrogation of Article 370. Her daughter, Iltija Mufti, was nominated but lost. Mehbooba's political journey continues amid ongoing challenges and demands for statehood restoration.
title: Mehbooba’s gamble: Price of political absence

description: Shagun Parihar, at 29, becomes the youngest winner of the 2024 J&K assembly elections with a victory in Kishtwar. Her win is marked by personal loss, with her father and uncle being victims of terrorism. Shagun vows to work towards peace and prosperity for her community.
title: Slain BJP man’s daughter wins terror-hit Kishtwar

description: Former jailer Suneel Sangwan, known for overseeing Haryana's high-security Sunaria jail housing Dera Sacha Sauda chief Gurmeet Ram Rahim, won his first election for the Charkhi Dadri assembly seat. Sangwan resigned from his post and joined BJP before running his campaign with a focus on district development.
title: Ram Rahim's former jailer posts win on 1st poll outing

description: In Jammu and Kashmir's first election in a decade, the National Conference (NC)-Congress alliance is poised to form the government, driven by Omar Abdullah's wins. The BJP saw gains, finishing second, while PDP faced a significant setback. The NC-Congress combination achieves a majority amidst a complex voting landscape, hinting at substantial political shifts in the region.
title: Abdullahs come in from the cold after 10 years

description: Over 50 senior doctors at RG Kar Medical College resigned in a symbolic protest, urging the Bengal government to address the deteriorating health of seven fasting junior doctors. The state government received no response, while faculty from other hospitals issued similar resignation threats. The junior doctors presented a 10-point charter of demands to the government.
title: 50 RG Kar doctors 'quit' in symbolic protest

description: BJP clinches a significant victory in Haryana, credited to PM Modi, securing a third consecutive win and boosting morale ahead of key state elections. Meanwhile, the NC-Congress alliance achieves a landmark win in J&K post-Article 370 abrogation. Saini is likely to continue as CM of Haryana, while Omar Abdullah is set to become CM of J&K.
title: BJP 1, NC-Cong 1: Swings momentum back in BJP's favour ahead of other state battles

description: Congress's defeat in Haryana provides a reality check for INDIA coalition allies, prompting a more cooperative approach in upcoming state polls. Regional partners like Shiv Sena and AAP anticipate smoother negotiations for seat-sharing and leadership roles, reducing Congress's previously overconfident stance.
title: Congress' loss may give allies edge in Maharashtra, Jharkhand talks

description: PM Narendra Modi accused Congress and its allies of joining international conspiracies to destabilize India and tarnish its institutions. He claimed Congress sought to divide the nation and undermine democracy. He hailed Haryana's electoral victory as a rejection of these tactics, stressing that development and unity triumphed over divisive politics.
title: J&K results victory for democracy; Hry befitting reply to Cong’s lies: PM Modi

description: The US has approved the sale of 53 MK-54 lightweight torpedoes worth $175 million to India for its MH-60R Seahawk helicopters. This move, aimed at bolstering India's anti-submarine capabilities and strategic bilateral ties, highlights India's role in maintaining stability in the Indo-Pacific region.
title: US okays sale of torpedoes worth $175m to India

description: Former WWE employee Janel Grant has sued WWE, Vince McMahon, and John Laurinaitis for sexual battery, harassment, and human trafficking. Grant alleges McMahon coerced her into a sexual relationship and directed her to engage with others. Her lawyer demands WWE release NDAs to let victims speak, claiming NDAs silence survivors and protect abusers. McMahon denies the allegations.
title: Lawsuit against Vince McMahon and WWE: Janel Grant's attorney calls for transparency

description: BJP President JP Nadda lauded PM Modi for party's success in the Haryana Assembly elections, attributing victories to public trust in Modi's leadership. Nadda criticizes Congress and AAP for misinformation and corruption. He underscores BJP's ambition to win upcoming elections in Maharashtra, Jharkhand, and Delhi, urging party members to maintain unity and dedication.
title: 'Haryana win reflects voters' trust': BJP chief Nadda hails PM Modi

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi addressed BJP workers at the party's headquarters after a significant victory in the Haryana assembly elections. The BJP will form the state government for the third time after winning 48 of the 90 seats. Modi emphasized that the victory represents progress and good governance, receiving support from all sections of society.
title: Congress has stooped to spreading poison in name of castes: PM Modi
'Vikas ki guarantee': PM Modi's calls Cong 'parasite' after Haryana, J&K results

description: Pakistan's PM Shehbaz Sharif vows not to allow the PTI party to disrupt the upcoming SCO Head of States' Summit. Sharif denounces PTI for causing chaos and failing to fulfill its election pledges, and highlights the stringent security measures for the event and the Chinese Premier's visit.
title: 'Won't allow PTI to ...': Shehbaz warns Imran ahead of SCO summit

description: Rhea Ripley missed winning the Women's World Championship due to Raquel Rodriguez's interference at Bad Blood. Ripley might seek revenge on Raquel, attempt another shot at the title against Liv Morgan, or team up with Damian Priest, her 'Terror Twins' partner, to confront Raquel's new alliance involving Dominik and Morgan.
title: What’s next for Rhea Ripley after the "Bad Blood" debacle?
Exit polls miss the mark, again: Haryana, J&K results prove pollsters wrong

description: Early trends in Haryana showed Congress leading and prompted celebrations with jalebis. However, BJP defied exit poll predictions, reversing the trend and ultimately securing a third term in power. This led BJP to send jalebis to Rahul Gandhi, mocking Congress’s initial optimism. Now that the BJP has stormed back to power for the unprecedented third time in the state, the Jalebi has taken centre stage in Haryana's political parley so much so that the party has ordered the sweet for Congress leader Rahul Gandhi.
title: How Jalebi ended up in Haryana's political platter?

description: Harsh Goenka supports Ola founder Bhavish Aggarwal in his online spat with comedian Kunal Kamra over Ola's electric scooter service issues. Kamra's tweets highlighted poor service conditions at Ola centres, prompting a show-cause notice from the Central Consumer Protection Authority. Despite an initial share dip, Ola Electric’s shares rose by 5.11% on Tuesday.
title: Harsh Goenka tags Ola founder Bhavish Aggarwal in this ‘kamra’ post

description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce confirmed their relationship in September 2023, with Swift attending key Chiefs games. Kelce's performance trends show higher stats with Swift present. Fans and analysts are keenly monitoring whether her attendance impacts his on-field performance amid the Chiefs' bid for another Super Bowl.
title: Exploring The Kansas City Chiefs’ TE Travis Kelce's Stats With And Without His Girlfriend Taylor Swift's Attendance
Historic hat-trick: CM Saini leads BJP to 'nayab' victory in Haryana
5 reasons why BJP's victory in Haryana is significant

description: Donald Trump's recent remarks, claiming that illegal immigrants have 'bad genes' and targeting Kamala Harris, sparked widespread outrage. Critics labeled his comments as eugenics and racist, reminiscent of Nazi ideologies. Trump's inflammatory language and sexist attacks on Harris have drawn condemnation, with many calling his rhetoric dangerous and hateful.
title: Herr Trump says Kamala is allowing 'bad genes' into America

description: The 2025 ICC Champions Trophy Final may be relocated from Lahore to Dubai if India qualifies for it, amid ongoing doubts about India's participation in Pakistan. Both countries' strained relations and past events are prompting consideration of alternate venues. PCB remains confident about hosting all matches in Pakistan, despite previous disruptions like the Asia Cup relocation.
title: 'Champions Trophy final to be held in Dubai if India qualify'

description: Former Jammu and Kashmir chief minister Omar Abdullah's decision to contest the assembly elections pays off as his party, National Conference, emerges as the largest with 42 seats. Omar Abdullah wins both Ganderbal and Budgam, securing his position as the next chief minister.
title: J&K polls: Omar Abdullah scripts stunning success story

description: BJP secures a historic win in Haryana, setting the stage for a third consecutive term by winning 48 out of 90 seats. Meanwhile, the NC-Congress alliance leads in Jammu and Kashmir with 48 seats, while Congress faces setbacks. BJP's victory is a boost ahead of Maharashtra, Jharkhand elections.
title: J&K, Haryana assembly election results: 10 key takeaways
How BJP managed to pull off the impossible in Haryana

description: Amazon has mandated a return to a five-day office workweek, citing young employees' need for in-office mentorship. This policy, defended by HR chief Beth Galetti, seeks a return to pre-pandemic norms with some flexibility. CEO Andy Jassy emphasized the benefits of office collaboration while some employees expressed concerns over commuting and work-life balance.
title: Amazon defends 5-day work from office policy

description: Today's entertainment highlights include the 70th National Film Awards honoring Mithun Chakraborty and other cinematic achievements, the anticipated launch of 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3' trailer, and shooting updates on 'War 2.' Additionally, Bhansali recalls his first meeting with Deepika Padukone, and Hania Aamir shares moments from Diljit Dosanjh's concert.
title: Read: Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: Ola, Uber, and Porter have failed to uphold fair working conditions for gig workers, says a Fairwork India report. Only bigbasket and Urban Company met minimum wage policies. Despite increased worker collectivization, no platform recognized collective groups. Companies like Amazon Flex and Swiggy earned points for safety equipment and training.
title: Ola, Uber, Porter lack fair working conditions for gig workers: Report

description: In an unprecedented leak, Russia-based YouTubers have reportedly obtained and unboxed Apple's unannounced M4 MacBook Pro. Expected to launch in November, these 14-inch devices demonstrate performance improvements. A significant warehouse leakage is suspected, with one seller claiming to have 200 units. Apple has yet to confirm the authenticity of these leaks.
title: Russian YouTubers call video on upcoming M4 MacBook Pro 'biggest leak'

description: Congress MP Kumari Selja expressed disappointment over Haryana election results, calling for a fresh start and identification of those responsible for the party's shortcomings. Despite intense campaigns by senior leaders, the BJP appeared set for a third consecutive term in the state.
title: 'Huge Disappointment': Congress MP Selja on Haryana polls results

description: In Delhi, UPI-related frauds topped financial scams in the first half of 2024 with 25,924 complaints. Techniques included fake payment screenshots, 'friend in need' scams, and malicious QR codes. Delhi Police urge users to verify transactions and avoid sharing sensitive information.
title: Delhi Police shares 5 most-common techniques used to scam people

description: The Union Ayush ministry declared advertising Ayurveda, Siddha, Unani, and Homeopathy drugs with "miraculous or supernatural effects" illegal, highlighting the risk to public health from unverified claims. The ministry urged the public to consult registered practitioners before using these drugs and to report any misleading advertisements or false claims. Self-diagnosis and self-medication are strongly discouraged.
title: 'Illegal': Centre on Ayurveda, Homeopathy drug ads claiming 'miraculous' effects

description: The assembly elections in Haryana and Jammu and Kashmir saw a historic win for BJP in Haryana, securing a record third term, while the National Conference and Congress alliance triumphed in Jammu and Kashmir. The elections in J&K were notable for their high participation, despite recent political changes.
title: Biggest winners and losers of this election season

description: MP Jairam Ramesh claims the Congressional defeat in the Haryana assembly elections was due to system misuse, not genuine loss, and announced plans to submit complaints to the Election Commission. Congressional leaders also highlighted the Jammu and Kashmir elections, expressing optimism for a coalition government despite challenges.
title: 'Cong has been made to lose ... ': Jairam on Haryana results

description: The 70th National Film Awards celebrated Indian cinema's best in New Delhi, honoring key winners like Mani Ratnam, Rishab Shetty, and Nithya Menen. 'KGF 2' won Best Feature Film Kannada, and 'Aattam' claimed Best Film. The ceremony highlighted the diversity and talent in regional films, with stars donning traditional attire and interacting amiably.
title: Mani Ratnam, AR Rahman, others receive National Award from President Murmu

description: Infosys has changed its hiring process to a more secure, paperless system, requiring candidates to access job details through the internal platform, aiming to tackle fraud and improve the experience.
title: Why Infosys is not issuing job offers via emails now

description: Former captain Nasser Hussain orchestrated Sachin Tendulkar’s only Test stumping in the third Test of England's 2001 tour of India. Tendulkar, on 90 runs, was frustrated by Ashley Giles' defensive bowling, leading to a rare stumping by James Foster. This strategic maneuver resulted in Tendulkar's only stumping in his 200-Test career.
title: How Nasser masterminded Sachin's only Test stumping

description: The WHO has praised India for eliminating trachoma, a contagious bacterial eye infection. Strong government leadership played a key role in this success. Trachoma, which can lead to blindness, was prevalent in areas with poor sanitation. The infection is preventable and treatable with antibiotics and better hygiene. India joins Nepal, Myanmar, and Pakistan in achieving this feat.
title: India awarded by WHO for eliminating trachoma: Know about the disease

description: Gulmohar, starring Manoj Bajpayee and Sharmila Tagore, won three honors at the 70th National Film Awards. Bajpayee expressed gratitude for receiving his fourth National Award, making it extra special as his wife attends the ceremony for the first time. The event will be held today in Delhi, starting at 3 PM.
title: Manoj Bajpayee wins National Film Award for the 4th time

description: The Election Commission of India has firmly rejected Congress's allegations of delays in updating Haryana Assembly election results on its website. Congress's Jairam Ramesh claimed the delay fosters misleading narratives; however, the ECI assured adherence to proper procedures. Trends show BJP leading in Haryana, while the Congress-NC alliance leads in Jammu and Kashmir.
title: 'Malafide narratives': EC rejects Congress's 'slow' update of results charge

description: Mayank Yadav made his T20I debut for India against Bangladesh but didn't hit his usual 150 kph speed due to caution post-injury. Aakash Chopra noted Mayank's control and potential despite the lower speed. In his impressive debut, Mayank had figures of 4-1-21-1 as India secured a 7-wicket win, leading the series 1-0.
title: Why Mayank didn't touch 150 clicks on debut vs B'desh?

description: India's T20I captain Suryakumar Yadav is close to equalling Virat Kohli's record to become the second-fastest player to score 2500 T20I runs. With 2461 runs in 72 matches, he needs 39 more runs in the second T20I against Bangladesh. India's strong performance in the first T20I sets the stage for Suryakumar's potential milestone.
title: SKY needs 39 runs to equal Kohli’s record and become...
'Satyanaash hi hoga': Brij Bhushan Singh reacts to Vinesh Phogat's win

description: Yuvraj Singh made his debut in Nairobi during the ICC Knockout under Sourav Ganguly's captaincy. Ganguly recalled instructing a security guard to ensure Yuvraj, then just 17 years old, stayed in his room by 9:30 pm. This precaution was to keep the young player focused for the games, reflecting Ganguly’s dedication to the team's performance.
title: When Ganguly asked a security guard to watch over Yuvraj

description: A US jury has found Cognizant guilty of discriminating against non-Indian workers, ordering the company to pay punitive damages. The lawsuit accused Cognizant of misusing the H-1B visa program and favoring South Asian workers, resulting in the dismissal of non-South Asian employees.
title: Cognizant guilty of discrimination against non-Indians, rules US court

description: Senior faculty at RG Kar Medical College have submitted mass resignations to support junior doctors protesting the rape and murder of a trainee. Despite government appeals, the junior doctors remain firm in their demands for justice, security, and administrative accountability, including the removal of the Health Secretary and establishment of student council elections.
title: 50 senior doctors of RG Kar resign in support of junior docs' hunger strike

description: BJP's Shagun Parihar won the Kishtwar seat in Jammu and Kashmir by 521 votes, defeating Sajjad Ahmed Kichloo of the National Conference. Parihar aimed to unify the region's communities impacted by terrorism. BJP's decision to nominate Shagun Parihar as their candidate was a strategic move to garner support from the district's diverse religious demographics.
title: BJP’s Shagun, whose father, uncle were killed by terrorists, wins Kishtwar

description: BJP's Shehzad Poonawalla criticises Congress for shifting from celebrating Haryana election victory to questioning the Election Commission's credibility over voter data discrepancies. Congress leaders Pawan Khera and Jairam Ramesh allege inconsistent vote counts and data reporting delays, suggesting attempts to influence local administration.
title: 'At 8:30am distributing Jalebis, at 11:30am criticising EC': BJP's jibe at Cong

description: Arvind Kejriwal emphasizes caution, noting that the lesson from Haryana's early poll trends favoring the BJP is to avoid overconfidence in elections. Despite AAP’s efforts and independent contesting of 89 seats after disagreements with Congress, they are trailing significantly. Kejriwal urges AAP councillors to focus on basic issues like garbage collection for the upcoming Delhi Assembly polls.
title: Biggest lesson from Haryana is never be overconfident: Arvind Kejriwal

description: John J Hopfield and Geoffrey E Hinton have won the Nobel Prize in Physics 2024 for their pivotal work in machine learning with artificial neural networks. Their innovations allow computers to mimic memory and learning functions, laying the groundwork for contemporary artificial intelligence advancements.
title: 2024 Nobel prize: John J Hopfield, Geoffrey E Hinton receive Physics award

description: Aamir Khan's video call with wrestler Vinesh Phogat after her performance at the Paris 2024 Olympics fueled speculation of a 'Dangal' sequel. He praised her resilience, calling her matches a testament to her champion mentality. Fans quickly expressed their excitement online, seeing a sequel as a natural progression to highlight the Phogat family legacy.
title: Aamir Khan’s video call with Vinesh Phogat sparked hopes for ‘Dangal 2’

description: During the 92nd anniversary parade of the Indian Air Force at Tambaram Air Force Station in Chennai, at least two air warriors fainted due to the extreme heat. This incident occurred shortly after five spectators died from sunstroke at a separate event. Despite the heat, the parade continued with aerobatic displays by Sukhoi and Tejas aircraft.=
title: 2 air warriors swooned during parade at Chennai IAF station

description: Farooq Abdullah announced Omar Abdullah as the new chief minister following a National Conference and Congress alliance victory in the Jammu and Kashmir assembly election. Omar secured a significant win in Budgam, and NC is leading with 43 seats. This is the first election since the abrogation of Article 370.
title: 'Omar Abdullah will be CM', says Farooq Abdullah as NC-Congress cross majority
Haryana assembly elections result: Constituency-wise winners list
Jammu & Kashmir assembly election: Constituency-wise winners list

description: The renowned singer Tulsi Kumar who has won millions of hearts with her soulful voice, gets injured on the sets while she was shooting for her new music video. A video of Tulsi Kumar from the set of her new music video has gone viral on social media. In the clip, she is seen performing in front of the camera when the shed behind her suddenly collapses.
title: Tulsi Kumar gets injured on the set of her new music video

description: Tennis has seen remarkable records that seem nearly unbeatable. Rafael Nadal's 14 French Open titles, Martina Navratilova's nine Wimbledon crowns, Steffi Graf's Calendar Golden Slam, Roger Federer's 237 weeks as World No. 1, and the 24 Grand Slam singles titles by Margaret Court and Novak Djokovic, highlight absolute dominance and extraordinary consistency in the sport.
title: Top five near-unbeatable records in tennis history

description: Qantas flight QF59 from Sydney to Tokyo played an adult-rated movie on all screens in the in-flight entertainment system.
title: Adult film plays on all screens in Qantas Flight; airline apologises

description: Anuradha Tiwari, CEO of Just Burst Out, faces criticism and support after posting images of her car with 'Brahmin genes' stickers on X.
title: Bengaluru CEO gets 'Brahmin genes' stamped on car

description: Congress party raised concerns to the Election Commission over delays in updating Haryana assembly election results on the ECI website, which could impact counting outcomes. It accused BJP of spreading misleading trends to pressure administration. EC refuted, asserting updates every 5 minutes.
title: Cong writes to EC, alleges 'inordinate' delay in updating trends for Haryana

description: Nayanthara and Vignesh Shivan, who married in June 2022, will soon have their wedding documentary released on an OTT platform. Fans eagerly await the 80-minute film capturing their romantic journey and wedding highlights. The couple also welcomed twins via surrogacy in October 2022.
title: Nayanthara and Vignesh Shivan's wedding documentary to have an OTT release soon

description: Aakash Chopra advises Delhi Capitals to retain all-rounder Axar Patel as their second retention for IPL 2025 due to his consistent performance. He also suggests making Rishabh Pant the first retention and considers options for the third spot, including Jake Fraser-McGurk and Kuldeep Yadav. He highlights retaining Abishek Porel as an uncapped player.
title: IPL: Chopra suggests DC to retain this player along with Rishabh Pant

description: Vipul Goel of the BJP leads in Faridabad Assembly with a significant 8,126-vote margin over Lakhan Kumar Singla of the INC. The constituency has recorded a 53% voter turnout. INLD's Narender Pal Singh Baghel falls far behind with only 462 votes.
title: Faridabad constituency result: BJP's Vipul Goel leads with over 8,000 votes

description: Ola CEO Bhavish Aggarwal's online spat with comedian Kunal Kamra coincides with Ola Electric facing a show-cause notice from the Central Consumer Protection Authority. The notice stems from over 10,000 customer complaints regarding service delays, manufacturing defects, and other issues. Ola Electric's shares have seen significant drops, with Aggarwal promising improvements.
title: Ola Electric gets show cause notice over consumer complaints

description: Israel announced on Monday that it had conducted an airstrike killing Suhail Hussein Husseini, Hezbollah's headquarters commander. He played a crucial role in managing logistics, budget, and weapons transfers between Iran and Hezbollah, as well as overseeing the group’s military operations and precision-guided missile development.
title: Who is Suhail Husseini? Hezbollah HQ's commander killed by Israel

description: Fatima, 22, marries a man nearly thrice her age to fund her grandmother's hospital stay and her sister's education. Meanwhile, Justice Lokur's inquiry commission on power deals faces uncertainties, with its term set to end on October 31 without clear progress.
title: Infamous ‘bride bazaar’ of Hyderabad takes digital turn

description: India's women's cricket team faces a challenging path in the ICC Women's T20 World Cup after a heavy loss to New Zealand and a win against Pakistan. Their chances of advancing depend on the outcome of the New Zealand-Australia match, necessitating wins in their remaining games to better their net run rate and secure a semifinal spot.
title: Women's T20 WC: How result of NZ vs AUS will impact India's semis chances

description: Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli, known for their love of football, often use the sport for warm-ups and fitness routines. They showcase their football skills during friendly games and charity matches, blending sportsmanship and competitive spirit, as seen in viral videos and social media posts.
title: Watch: Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli show off their football skills

description: In the closely contested Haryana assembly elections, early trends show BJP and Congress neck and neck, with BJP slightly leading. The Congress is poised for a comeback, focusing on unemployment and agrarian distress. Notably, Bhupinder Singh Hooda and Vinesh Phogat are leading in their respective constituencies.
title: Haryana and J&K assembly election results: Who is leading/trailing
Uchana Kalan poll results: Dushyant Chautala trailing
Sopore assembly election result: NC's Irshad Rasool Kar leads
Bijbehara assembly constituency: PDP's Iltija Mufti trailing

description: A LinkedIn post by Torrey Leonard features his co-founder Casey Mackrell working on his laptop during his own wedding, sparking mixed reactions. While some criticized it as embarrassing, others praised his dedication and commitment to their AI startup Thoughtly, highlighting the challenges founders face in balancing work and personal life.
title: AI startup founder takes laptop to work on his wedding day; internet divided

description: Indian hockey midfielder Hardik Singh humorously questioned the quality of his Paris 2024 Olympic bronze medal, doubting its composition. Hardik expressed disappointment during a podcast appearance. He also highlighted the recognition issues faced by athletes in India, sharing an incident where his team was overlooked in favor of a social media personality.
title: 'Iron from Eiffel Tower...': Hardik questions 'quality' of Paris Olympic medal

description: Indian cricket legend Sachin Tendulkar's participation in the 1990s Hong Kong Cricket Sixes highlighted the tournament's popularity. After a seven-year hiatus, the event returns this November, with Team India joining the 20th edition, promising an exciting display of quick, high-scoring cricket.
title: When Sachin Tendulkar played in the Hong Kong Cricket Sixes
Haryana assembly election: Vinesh Phogat leads from Julana in early trends
Karnal assembly constituency: BJP's Jagmohan Anand leading

description: Google DeepMind is utilizing its Gemini AI model to manage up to 50% of legal information requests, significantly boosting efficiency. Similarly, Bayer's pharmaceuticals division uses AI for 70% to 80% of regulatory filings, underscoring AI's role in enhancing organizational processes without eliminating human jobs.
title: Google DeepMind exec shares what the company uses AI for 'big time'

description: Indian cricketer Axar Patel announced his wife Meha's pregnancy through an Instagram video, garnering many congratulatory messages. The couple, who married in January 2023, joyfully prepares for their first child. Axar has been rested from the T20I series against Bangladesh, allowing him to spend time with his family.
title: Watch: Axar reveals wife Meha's pregnancy with a heartwarming video

description: The Centre has begun selling tomatoes at Rs 65 per kg in 50 locations across New Delhi to address a price surge ahead of the festive season, driven by monsoon rains and humidity affecting production in major states. This intervention might soon extend to other cities.
title: Centre to start selling tomatoes at Rs 65/kg in Delhi as prices surge

description: CISCE will introduce robotics and AI for Classes XI and XII from 2025-26, integrating these subjects at the elementary level with computer science. The holistic progress card, competency-based questions, and digital assessments will align with the National Education Policy 2020. These changes aim to foster creativity, innovation, and critical thinking across over 30 lakh students.
title: India Inc must create more jobs: Manasi Kirloskar

description: Auto retail sales in India saw a 9% decline in September due to high passenger vehicle inventory and weak demand. Passenger vehicle sales dropped 19%, while two-wheeler registrations fell by 8%. Commercial vehicle registrations declined 10%, though tractor sales saw a 15% increase despite overall sluggish market conditions.
title: Auto retail sales skid 9% in Sept on sluggish demand

description: Hero Motors has retracted its IPO plan worth Rs 900 crore, as indicated in an update with Sebi. The proposed IPO included a fresh issue to raise Rs 500 crore and an OFS worth Rs 400 crore by promoters. Proceeds were intended for debt payment and facility expansion.
title: Hero Motors withdraws documents for Rs 900cr IPO

description: Shakib Al Hasan, Bangladesh's cricket icon, might fulfill his wish to play his farewell Test at home as top officials show support. Youth and Sports advisor Asif Mahmud Shojib Bhuyain endorsed this, promising top-notch security for Shakib. Despite his political challenges, the Bangladesh Cricket Board aims to include him in the Test series against South Africa.
title: Shakib Al Hasan's farewell Test in Bangladesh could become reality

description: Indian cricketer Hardik Pandya dedicates time to his son Agastya after separating from Natasa Stankovic, sharing heartwarming moments on social media. Currently part of India's T20I squad against Bangladesh, Pandya's impressive performance includes an unbeaten 39-run knock that led India to victory in the first match.
title: Watch: Hardik Pandya's heartwarming moment with son Agastya

description: Sanju Samson, aiming for a permanent spot in the Indian cricket team, opened against Bangladesh in the T20I series under new leadership. Despite a promising start, he was dismissed for 29 runs. Aakash Chopra stressed the need for consistency to avoid being dropped, praising Samson's elegant shot-making but urging him to capitalize on opportunities.
title: 'They would drop him': Former India opener's warning for Sanju Samson

description: In Bengaluru, Mohammad Fayazuddin and his 15-year-old stepdaughter were caught after stealing over 40 bicycles. Using the girl to avoid suspicion and evade punishments, Fayazuddin aimed to offset his financial debts. Police recovered 22 bicycles, with the minor returned to her mother's custody.
title: Stepdad uses daughter, 15, to steal over 40 bicycles in Bengaluru

description: A U.S. judge has mandated Google to open Android to rival third-party app stores and allow them to manage app transactions independently. The ruling results from Epic Games' 2020 lawsuit, aiming to counter Google's monopolistic control over app distribution and in-app payments on Android devices. Google is told to allow alternative app stores to operate on Android devices starting November 1, 2024 for three years.
title: Epic ‘win’: 5 changes Google has to bring after judge tells it to open Android to rivals

description: An FIR has been filed against Alt News co-founder Mohammad Zubair for allegedly inciting protests against Dasna Devi temple priest Yati Narsinghanand. Zubair's posts allegedly led to a demonstration, prompting police to impose prohibitory orders. The charges against Zubair include promoting enmity and defamation. Ten protesters were arrested amid heightened security and tension in Ghaziabad.
title: Priest Yati Narsinghanand facing 2 FIRs for hate speech untraceable

description: Bharti Airtel is in advanced talks with Tata Group to acquire Tata Play, aiming to consolidate its digital TV presence and enhance bundled offerings. This acquisition follows Bharti's 2017 purchase of Tata's consumer mobility business and addresses the growing competition and decline in DTH services due to OTT platforms.
title: Bharti Airtel may buy another 'loss-making' Tata Group company, after 7 yrs

description: Lin Yunyun, a seller on China's e-commerce platform Pinduoduo, faces constant pressure to cut diaper prices to maintain visibility. The platform's aggressive discount strategy reflects China's broader deflation woes, driven by economic anxiety and reduced consumer spending.
title: How online shopping websites' price wars may hurt Chinese economy

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 8, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope Today, October 8, 2024: Read your today's astrological predictions
